div.span: This is a state description of HR600 Workflow
There is still unsaved production data in the backup directory.Do you want to transfer the data to the network drive now?
There is production data in the backup directory that has not yet been backed up.The network drive for backing up the data is not available.The data cannot be transferred.

The transfer of the packed production data export file failed.The data will be saved to a local backup directory.Please make sure that the network drive is available and access is granted.You can move the cached data to the network drive again the next time you start HRSoft2.

The backup of the packed production data export file to the backup directory failed.Please make sure that the backup directory is available and access is granted.You may find the production data unpacked on the temporary directory TempArchiveFiles.You can also initiate a manual export from the HRSoft2 archives.If the problem persists, please contact Ersa service.

An error occurred while generating the zip file of the production data.The generation of the production data is aborted.You can continue the process normally until the end.You can perform a manual file-based data backup to a network driveby performing an export in the archive in the archive entry just generated.If this problem persists, please contact Ersa Service.

An error occurred while generating the CSV data.The generation of the production data is aborted.You can continue the process normally until the end.You can perform a manual file-based data backup to a network driveby performing an export in the archive in the archive entry just created.If this problem persists, please contact Ersa Service.

An error occurred while querying the database for the last entry.The generation of the production data is aborted.You can continue the process normally until the end.You can perform a manual file-based data backup to a network driveby performing an export in the archive in the archive entry just generated.If this problem persists, please contact Ersa Service.
